         <entryFree xml:id="k000116" type="architectural feature">
            <term xml:id="term-k000116-9" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt">fang</term>          
            <term xml:id="term-k000116-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">方</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000116-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">方</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000116-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin">fāng</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000116-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">fang</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000116-6" xml:lang="en" type="literal_translation">square; square-shaped (beam or joist) (lit.)</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000116-7" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000116-2">lintel</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000116-8" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000116-3">rafter plate; a horizontal structural member under and parallel to the purlins</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000116-1" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000116-1">squared beams</term>
            <note type="Note">
               <p xml:lang="en">As used in the in the <title ref="https://tinyurl.com/y3ypdndz">Yingzao fashi</title> (1103) to define a building component, the fang 方 is a structural timber whose cross-section measurement is based on a single standard modular unit (dancai) of the larger building. Its application is relatively flexible, and the term is often modified by the names of locations where it is used within the building. <s source="#biblk000116-4">In the <term ref="/keyword/k000070">Qing</term> dynasty the character <term ref="/keyword/k000117">fang 枋</term> encompasses the architectural use of the character 方.</s></p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant"><term ref="/keyword/k000074">宋</term><title ref="https://tinyurl.com/y3ypdndz">營造法式</title>中， 方則指 斷面尺寸一單材為基準的小斷面構建，使用較靈活， 一所處位置有不同的名稱。</p>  
            </note>
            <note type="related concept"><term ref="/keyword/k000114">é 額</term></note>
